y customers and community members to drive roadmaps Review and approve the roadmaps submitted by product managers Mentor product managers and give feedback on their work \u2014 user research, product requirement documents, field engagement, roadmaps, etc. Partner with the marketing, design, and agile development teams to deliver on the roadmap Communicate product status to all internal and external stakeholders, including VP of Product Strategy and senior leadership Act as a key product advocate, presenting at public forums and in front of customers, partners, and investors Keep sales and marketing updated on feature releases and engineering on feature requests Orchestrate technical sales training for pre-sales engineers Help with sales and marketing collateral to educate on the product story and features (website copy, white papers, sales decks, FAQs, etc.) Minimum Qualifications (knowledge, Skills, And Abilities) Strong user and market research skills Ability to organize multiple stakeholders toward a common goal Strong technical acumen with a solid understanding of the security market Knowledge of regulatory and compliance issues is a plus Humility and learning mindset Information seeking and data-driven Ability to explain complex ideas simply Strong written, verbal, and visual communication skills Strong project management and/or organizational skills Good working knowledge of agile development processes and roles Education/Experience Bachelor's degree, preferably in software engineering or computer science Minimum of 10 years' experience in the software industry 5+ years as a senior technical product manager managing other product managers Experience leading product portfolios with $20m+ annual revenue 3+ years of product management experience with blockchain-based products 3+ years' experience with lean agile software development practices required Experience with managing open source products preferred but not required Background experience as a practicing so